Liverpool midfielder Philippe Coutinho has put pen to paper on a new five-year contract at the club.The 24-year-old joined the club in 2013 for only &pound;8.5 million and has since grown into a star player for the Merseyside outfit.The Brazilian was delighted to commit his future to the Reds and is now tied down until 2022, extending his stay by two years.&ldquo;I would like to thank everybody at the club, first of all,&rdquo; Coutinho told the club&rsquo;s official website.&ldquo;I am very happy to sign a new contract here. It is a club that I am very grateful to and this shows my happiness here. I will work much harder to repay the belief shown in me.&ldquo;I signed this new contract to stay here for a few more years because it&rsquo;s a great honour for me. It gives me great happiness because I was welcomed here with open arms by everyone at the club and the supporters right from my first day. I am very thankful to this football club for everything."